children.subject: that may be true, but my question still remains - what is 47B like?
As a transfer student, I think you should retake 61B, since the Data Structure course in CC is a joke, 61B is more rigorous, and also very useful for job interviews.

history.content:
Has anyone taken this before who can comment?  Just wondering what the the workload is like.  How does the class work, is it completely independent work?  How do I sign up, do I need to get some sort of add code from an advisor?

I took a Data Structures class at a CC 1.5 years ago.  For this particular CC, it wasn't required to do the 47B followup in order to get full credit for 61B.  It was a pretty good class actually, but I feel like I'm missing out on a bunch of stuff I'll need later if I don't do this.  I'm debating whether to take this with 3 technicals, or with 4 technicals.  CS61C is the only really time-consuming one out of the 3 or 4.
